Node.Notes: Many follow a number of Hebrew manuscripts and ancient versions in reading "his soul" instead of "my soul," which is in the Masoretic text. Those who read "my soul" explain it as referring to Yahweh's name.
Uncertain. Text reads "those who seek your face, Jacob." Many follow two Hebrew manuscripts, LXX, and Syriac in reading "the God for Jacob."
"Lift up the head" can mean rejoice, so uncertain whether gates are to be opened or are to rejoice.
